s: How firm a foundation
O come, all ye faithful
Lift every voice and sing
All through the night
Go, my children
For the fruit of all creation
God who made the earth and heaven

t: AS I WENT DOWN TO THE RIVER TO PRAY
s: As I went down to the river to pray
When the King shall come again
Come, ye faithful, raise the strain
We are people of God's peace
Come, humble sinner
Oh, for a closer walk
Come, Holy Spirit
The Lord's my shepherd
Help us to help each other, Lord
Be still and know
Receive our thanks
On Jordan's Stormy Banks
Hymn of Breaking Strain
Morning has broken
Child in the manger
Bwana awabariki (May God grant you a blessing)
Christ who left his home in glory
O holy city, seen of John
The King shall come when morning dawns
I walk the unfrequented road
Come, ye disconsolate
What a friend we have in Jesus
Now blessed be the Lord our God
All hail the power of Jesus' name
The Lord's my shepherd
How gentle God's commands
Blest be the tie that binds
O wondrous type! O vision fair
A hymn of glory let us sing
Sing we triumphant hymns
Forth in the peace of Christ we go
O love, how deep, how broad
All hail the power of Jesus' name
As with gladness men of old
Praise to God, immortal praise
God of mercy, God of grace
For the beauty of our earth
God moves in a mysterious way
O God of Bethel, by whose hand
Let saints on earth in concert sing
O God, we praise thee; and confess
Great God, how infinite art thou
The people that in darkness sat
I to the hills will lift my eyes
Christ the Lord is risen today
Jesus, tempted in the desert
God hath spoken by his prophets
Hear the turmoil of the nations
Once to every soul and nation
O the deep, deep love of Jesus
A mighty fortress is our God
I sing the mighty power of God
Hosanna, loud hosanna
Epitaph of Seikilos
Break forth, O beauteous heavenly light
Lo, how a Rose e'er blooming
Abide with me
Great is thy faithfulness
The Lord bless you and keep you
This is my song
Be still my soul
As the deer with eager yearning
Comfort, comfort, O my people
Angels we have heard on high
Glory be to the Father
When Israel was in Egypt's land
God be with you till we meet again
Teach me thy truth
What Child is this
Ask ye what great thing I know
Take my life, and let it be
O sacred Head, now wounded
God, who stretched the spangled heavens
All who hunger, gather gladly
Brethren, we have met to worship
Alleluia! Sing to Jesus
Love divine, all loves excelling
Come, thou long-expected Jesus
Sing a new world into being
Joyful, joyful, we adore thee
No matter if you live now far or near
Come, ye sinners, poor and wretched
Hark, I hear the harps eternal
Could it be that God is singing
Once in royal David's city
'Twas in the moon of wintertime
Religion fit to last
We three kings
I heard the voice of Jesus say
La paz de la tierra (The peace of the earth)
Singer of Life
Wakantanka (Many and Great)
All creatures of the earth and sky
All creatures worship God most high
Praise, my soul, the King of heaven
Praise with joy the world's Creator
Warm summer sun
The voice of God is calling
O Jesus, we adore thee
The morning hangs a signal
Ye Christian heralds, go proclaim
Let there be light
Summoned by the God who made us
Come, thou fount
Amazing grace
Heart with loving heart united
Jesus, refuge of the weary
Christian hearts in love united

t: O WELT, ICH MUSS DICH LASSEN
s: Now all the woods are sleeping
Let there be light
Praise God (Doxology)
May nothing evil cross this door
Bright those jewels
Loveliest of trees
Move in our midst
On Jordan's Stormy Banks
God be with you till we meet again
For the healing of the nations
Angels, from the realms of glory
My Shepherd will supply my need
No number tallies up my score
In the Rifted Rock (Wehrlos und verlassen)
O God, in restless living
The Sands of Time Are Sinking
Heilig, Heilig, Heilig (Holy, Holy, Holy)
Lord of the dance
'Tis a gift to be simple
Lord of all hopefulness
Be thou my vision
Oh the Praties they grow small
Step by step the longest march
Beloved, God's chosen
The works of the Lord are created in wisdom
In our day of thanksgiving
The day you gave us, Lord
Come, ye thankful people
O little town of Bethlehem
Come, thou long-expected Jesus
Grant us, God, the grace of giving
May we each take joy in giving
All praise to thee, my God
Calm soul of all things
I vow to thee, my country
O God beyond all praising
Come, my Way, my Truth, my Light
How shallow former shadows seem
To mock your reign, O dearest Lord
When rising from the bed of death
Breath on me, breath of God
When we walk with the Lord
O come, O come, Immanuel
Come, O thou Traveler unknown
Now, on land and sea descending
When Peace like a River
This joyful Eastertide
Wade in the water
Way way way
I am a poor wayfaring stranger
Say not the struggle naught availeth
We shall overcome
Now is the time approaching
There's a wideness in God's mercy
Now the day is over
Jesu, joy of our desiring
We plow the fields and scatter
Again the morn of gladness
God is here among us
Gott ist gegenwärtig
